  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations to New Jersey totaled $5B in FY2026 to date. Award activity reached 281,029 awards with an average award size of $17.9K, and obligations fell 46.0% year over year. Annual obligations were higher in prior fiscal years, with FY25 at $9.3B, FY24 at $9.8B, FY23 at $9.2B, FY22 at $9.3B, and FY21 at $8.9B. The Department of Defense accounted for the single largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $3B, followed by the Department of Veterans Affairs at $599M and the Department of Homeland Security at $550M. Top vendors by obligations in FY2026 to date include LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $972M, WHITING-TURNER CONTRACTING COMPANY, THE at $400M, and ASRC FEDERAL FACILITIES LOGISTICS, LLC at $396M. Major industry categories receiving obligations include Search, Detection, Navigation, Guidance, Aeronautical, and Nautical System and Instrument Manufacturing at $691M, Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $560M, and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $483M.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Where is federal spending in New Jersey concentrated?",
        "body": "Spending is concentrated with the Department of Defense at $3B in FY2026 to date, making it the largest buying agency in the state. The Department of Veterans Affairs at $599M and the Department of Homeland Security at $550M are the next-largest buyers. Overall obligations for FY2026 to date are $5B, down 46.0% year over year, compared with prior fiscal years that ranged from $8.9B to $9.8B."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What types of work and vendors are receiving obligations?",
        "body": "Top industries by obligations include Search, Detection, Navigation, Guidance, Aeronautical, and Nautical System and Instrument Manufacturing at $691M, Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $560M, and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $483M. Leading vendors are LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $972M, WHITING-TURNER CONTRACTING COMPANY, THE at $400M, and ASRC FEDERAL FACILITIES LOGISTICS, LLC at $396M. Award volume is high at 281,029 awards with an average award size of $17.9K."
      }
